# Ignore Visual Studio temporary files, build results, and user-specific files.

## Build folders
bin/
obj/

## Visual Studio
.vs/
*.user
*.suo
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates

## Rider
.idea/
*.sln.iml

## ReSharper
_ReSharper*/
*.DotSettings.user

## NuGet
*.nupkg
**/packages/*
!**/packages/build/

## Visual Studio Code
.vscode/
.history/

## OS Files
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

## Logs
*.log

## Coverage results
*.coverage
*.coveragexml
*.testscoverage
coverage.*

## Test results
TestResults/

## ASP.NET Scaffolding
ScaffoldingReadMe.txt

## Publish outputs
*.Publish.xml

## Build and generated files
*.cache
*.ilk
*.pdb
*.ipdb
*.iobj
*.tlog
*.lastbuildstate
*.err
*.vsp
*.vspx
*.sap
GeneratedMSBuildEditorConfig.editorconfig
project.assets.json

# Keep appsettings files in source control unless you intentionally want a local-only config.
# Do not ignore appsettings.json or appsettings.Development.json by default.